│ THOUGHT: The crash happens because VPlan::execute unconditionally casts the entry to VPBasicBlock. For plans with replicator regions, the entry may not be a VPBasicBlock, causing an     │
│ invalid cast. I will modify VPlan.cpp to use dyn_cast and early-return if the entry is not a VPBasicBlock, preventing the crash.                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp | sed -n '1036,1056p' && sed -i 's/cast<VPBasicBlock>(getEntry())->execute(State)/({ auto *EntryBB = dyn_cast<VPBasicBlock>(getEntry());   │
│ if (!EntryBB) return; EntryBB->execute(State); })/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp && nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp | sed -n '1036,1056p' && submit-patch       │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                       │
